A man has been charged with the murder of a man who was shot on a Merseyside street.Rikki Berry, 36, died in hospital after being shot on Quarryside Drive in Kirkby, Knowsley, on the evening of Wednesday 17 July.Merseyside Police said they had charged Adam Williams, 25, of Bigdale Drive, Kirkby.He was remanded in custody and scheduled to appear at Liverpool Magistrates' Court later, the force added.
Detectives said they had also arrested three people in Oswestry, Shropshire, on suspicion of murder and possession of a firearm on Wednesday.A 24-year-old man, of no fixed address, and a 21-year-old woman from Kirkby have both been bailed pending further inquiries.Police have renewed appeals for anyone with information, images or footage to contact them.
